<div class="rebranding_container block-flex-wrap block-flex-center-sb block-gap-30">
    <div class="dior-seo_codes-desc block-flex-wrap block-gap-40">
        <h2 class="h2-heading-ss w-100">
            Dior <span class="h2-heading-pp">date code</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="block-flex-wrap block-gap-20">
            <p class="caption tal">Newer bags (post-2000s):</p>
            <p class="body-text w-100">
                You can ignore the first two numbers — they're just control numbers.
<br><br>
The two letters indicate the country of manufacture (e.g., MA for Italy, MC for Spain).
<br><br>
The final four numbers reveal the production date.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="block-flex-wrap block-gap-20">
            <p class="caption tal">Vintage bags (late 1990s):</p>
            <p class="body-text w-100">
                The code may be more straightforward, consisting of just two letters followed by four numbers (e.g., MA-0959).
            </p>
        </div>
        <a class="rebranding_btn rebranding_btn-main m-0">
            Authenticate now
        </a>
